  "prompt": "What should I gift to my teacher?",
  "response": "Here are some thoughtful gift ideas for teachers:\n\n1. Practical gifts:\n- Gift cards (coffee shop, bookstore, office supply store)\n- Quality coffee mug\n- Personalized stationery\n- Desk accessories\n\n2. Classroom supplies:\n- Colorful markers or pens\n- Classroom decorations\n- Books for the classroom library\n\n3. Thoughtful personal gifts:\n- Handwritten thank you card\n- Homemade baked goods\n- Potted plant or succulent\n- Picture frame\n- Scented candle\n\n4. Experience gifts:\n- Small journal\n- Bookmarks\n- Tea or coffee sampler\n\n5. Budget-friendly options:\n- Handmade craft\n- School supplies\n- Personalized ornament\n- Small chocolate or candy assortment\n\nTips:\n- Check school guidelines about gift-giving\n- Consider your budget\n- Keep the gift simple and appropriate\n- A heartfelt thank you note can mean more than an expensive gift\n- Consider group gifts with classmates for higher-value items\n\nRemember, teachers appreciate thoughtful gestures that show you value their hard work and dedication.",
